1
00:00:00,502 --> 00:00:03,575
Now the story of a wealthy family who lost everything

2
00:00:03,632 --> 00:00:07,380
and the one son who had no choice but to keep them all together.

3
00:00:13,254 --> 00:00:15,162
It's... Arrested Development.

4
00:00:18,159 --> 00:00:21,548
Michael Bluth began his day with something he'd never seen before.

5
00:00:21,594 --> 00:00:23,667
I'm hearing good things about the Bluth Company. What do you think?

6
00:00:23,714 --> 00:00:25,886
Good news about his family's housing business.

7
00:00:25,930 --> 00:00:28,485
Old Man Bluth's in jail. I think his son is running the company.

8
00:00:28,541 --> 00:00:30,882
Doesn't seem like a total moron to me.

9
00:00:30,937 --> 00:00:32,975
You know what? I've had this thing as a triple sell,

10
00:00:33,017 --> 00:00:35,289
and I am upgrading it, right here, right now!

11
00:00:35,336 --> 00:00:38,971
I think this thing could even go as high as a "Don't Buy."

12
00:00:39,038 --> 00:00:40,281
"Don't Buy!"

13
00:00:40,363 --> 00:00:42,545
Huh? Mom, did you see that?

14
00:00:42,552 --> 00:00:43,784
Don't buy Bluth!

15
00:00:43,877 --> 00:00:46,595
You build a house that's good, people are going to want to come...

16
00:00:51,454 --> 00:00:53,523
The sinkhole spread a little bit more last night?

17
00:00:53,604 --> 00:00:55,186
Anyway, I'm going to go to the prison.

18
00:00:55,254 --> 00:00:56,799
I'm going to tell Dad about this news.

19
00:00:56,886 --> 00:00:58,540
I thought you said we shouldn't visit him.

20
00:00:58,616 --> 00:01:00,455
Uh, visit, no. Gloat, yes.

21
00:01:00,526 --> 00:01:03,722
I've worked very, very hard for this. I sold the cabin property to keep us afloat.

22
00:01:03,772 --> 00:01:05,815
I haven't had any time to spend with my son.

23
00:01:05,882 --> 00:01:08,458
Well, now you can spend time with my son.

24
00:01:08,539 --> 00:01:10,956
I want your brother Buster to come live with you.

25
00:01:11,013 --> 00:01:14,811
And it's not because he has that horrible hook for a hand now.

26
00:01:14,874 --> 00:01:15,871
It's the snoring.

27
00:01:15,952 --> 00:01:17,090
Listen to this.

28
00:01:17,165 --> 00:01:19,623
This is Buster snoring, Wednesday night.

29
00:01:21,101 --> 00:01:23,167
It's driving me craz...

30
00:01:23,277 --> 00:01:24,615
You won't even know he's here.

31
00:01:24,678 --> 00:01:26,931
You seem more villainous than usual, mom. Are you sober?

32
00:01:27,008 --> 00:01:28,763
Michael, it's 8:00 a.m.

33
00:01:28,836 --> 00:01:30,191
So it's not that.

34
00:01:31,170 --> 00:01:32,322
I don't know.

35
00:01:32,392 --> 00:01:35,430
Maybe it's because I went off my post-partum medication.

36
00:01:35,496 --> 00:01:38,513
You were still taking that? You had Buster 32 years ago.

37
00:01:38,590 --> 00:01:40,985
And that's how long I've been depressed about him.

38
00:01:41,144 --> 00:01:44,032
Actually, I did go off it in the early '90s,

39
00:01:44,078 --> 00:01:45,900
but I didn't like what happened to me.

40
00:01:45,967 --> 00:01:49,669
Claiming she could take it no more, the young mother released the emergency brake,

41
00:01:49,725 --> 00:01:53,606
allowing her car to roll backwards into the nearby lake.

42
00:01:53,692 --> 00:01:54,999
Good for her!

43
00:01:57,175 --> 00:01:58,910
I must have gained three pounds.

44
00:01:58,981 --> 00:02:00,476
Why'd you go off them this time?

45
00:02:00,563 --> 00:02:04,752
Well, apparently, mood-altering medication leads to street drugs.

46
00:02:04,839 --> 00:02:08,669
That's what this very handsome, young doctor said on The Today Show.

47
00:02:09,457 --> 00:02:11,787
That was Tom Cruise, the actor.

48
00:02:11,890 --> 00:02:14,664
They said he was some kind of scientist.

49
00:02:15,145 --> 00:02:16,917
Maybe you should get away from Buster.

50
00:02:17,010 --> 00:02:19,395
Why don't you go up to the cabin in the woods?

51
00:02:19,477 --> 00:02:20,870
I thought you said we sold it.

52
00:02:20,959 --> 00:02:23,927
We sold the property. I worked it out so that we could relocate the cabin,

53
00:02:23,999 --> 00:02:26,588
but it is going to be up in Tahoe for another couple of days.

54
00:02:26,661 --> 00:02:29,241
Maybe you can take a date up there.

55
00:02:29,503 --> 00:02:34,015
How am I supposed to find someone willing to go into that musty old claptrap?

56
00:02:37,710 --> 00:02:41,294
The cabin! Yes, th... well, that would be difficult, too.

57
00:02:43,040 --> 00:02:47,151
Please get back on the meds, Mom. We miss the old, old you.

58
00:02:49,194 --> 00:02:51,098
I didn't even know that we had a cabin.

59
00:02:51,208 --> 00:02:52,353
Ah, ( bleep ).

60
00:02:52,809 --> 00:02:55,794
Well, for what it's worth, Gob, I've never actually been there.

61
00:02:55,871 --> 00:02:57,679
Although he'd often been promised.

62
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:59,532
Hey, pal. Something's come up.

63
00:02:59,603 --> 00:03:01,969
This nice young lady has lost her puppy,

64
00:03:02,046 --> 00:03:03,811
and your dad's got to help her find him.

65
00:03:03,889 --> 00:03:05,922
Oh, bad news, buddy.

66
00:03:06,008 --> 00:03:08,096
This young lady's dad is sick, and...

67
00:03:08,298 --> 00:03:09,771
I'm taking her to the hospital.

68
00:03:09,844 --> 00:03:13,386
Come on, you're old enough to figure this out. I'm nailing this broad.

69
00:03:13,479 --> 00:03:16,367
Pardon me if I don't burst into tears, Michael,

70
00:03:16,443 --> 00:03:18,429
but at least he promised to take you.

71
00:03:18,783 --> 00:03:21,491
He just let me blindly enjoy my childhood.

72
00:03:22,085 --> 00:03:25,182
I didn't even know there was a cabin he wasn't taking me to!

73
00:03:25,302 --> 00:03:27,317
Hmm, mine's sadder.

74
00:03:27,389 --> 00:03:29,299
I don't see you crying, robot.

75
00:03:29,550 --> 00:03:30,826
You taste these tears.

76
00:03:30,928 --> 00:03:32,140
Taste my sad, Michael.

77
00:03:32,144 --> 00:03:33,939
I am not going to lick your eye, okay?

78
00:03:35,069 --> 00:03:36,907
Well, I will tell you this, Michael...

79
00:03:36,974 --> 00:03:37,906
I don't have a son...

80
00:03:37,978 --> 00:03:38,505
He does.

81
00:03:38,566 --> 00:03:41,982
But if I ever do, I'm either going to take him to the cabin in the woods,

82
00:03:42,069 --> 00:03:44,332
or I'm going to promise to take him and then not take him.

83
00:03:44,419 --> 00:03:47,937
But the one thing that I will never do is not tell him

84
00:03:47,982 --> 00:03:51,797
that I'm taking him to a cabin in the woods, and then not take him!

85
00:03:51,859 --> 00:03:53,461
Gob was growing up.

86
00:03:53,758 --> 00:03:57,208
Well, the cabin in the woods is going to be stacked up next to our carport.

87
00:03:57,327 --> 00:04:00,281
But... maybe we should head up there tonight, huh?

88
00:04:00,364 --> 00:04:03,159
One first time...

89
00:04:04,541 --> 00:04:06,389
Taste the happy, Michael.

90
00:04:06,609 --> 00:04:07,541
Taste it.

91
00:04:07,711 --> 00:04:09,231
Tastes kind of like sad.

92
00:04:09,323 --> 00:04:13,635
Michael set off to prison, to tell off his father, when he discovered his son.

93
00:04:13,706 --> 00:04:14,715
George Michael?

94
00:04:15,027 --> 00:04:16,004
Dad. Hey.

95
00:04:16,077 --> 00:04:16,833
What are you doing?

96
00:04:16,906 --> 00:04:19,487
I didn't want to miss you because you've been leaving so early lately.

97
00:04:19,548 --> 00:04:20,970
You slept out here to see me?

98
00:04:21,078 --> 00:04:24,930
Michael had never been so touched by something his son had said...

99
00:04:25,042 --> 00:04:26,296
but it wasn't true.

100
00:04:26,417 --> 00:04:29,972
He was hiding from his cousin, after an awkward incident.

101
00:04:33,218 --> 00:04:35,262
They'd since been trying to avoid each other,

102
00:04:35,347 --> 00:04:38,539
which was difficult, considering they shared a bunk bed.

103
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:42,829
- Oh, hi.
- Hi.

104
00:04:44,615 --> 00:04:46,501
- I'm off to the car.
- I'll be in the crawl space.

105
00:04:46,510 --> 00:04:48,563
Tell you what. How would you like to head up to the cabin?

106
00:04:48,805 --> 00:04:50,274
Can you afford to skip work?

107
00:04:50,354 --> 00:04:54,529
I think the president of a "Don't Buy" company can afford to take a day off.

108
00:04:54,626 --> 00:04:56,090
We're up from "Sell"?

109
00:04:57,138 --> 00:04:59,188
- It's happening, isn't it?
- It's really happening.

110
00:04:59,362 --> 00:05:01,327
And it's time for us to start creating some memories.

111
00:05:01,384 --> 00:05:03,621
You know, there's been enough disappointment in this family.

112
00:05:07,604 --> 00:05:11,173
There's only one sleeping bag, so we're going to have to double up.

113
00:05:11,251 --> 00:05:15,464
Sorry, pal, something came up.

114
00:05:16,769 --> 00:05:17,977
It is worse to know.

115
00:05:18,092 --> 00:05:20,968
Gob was getting life lessons all over the place.

116
00:05:21,005 --> 00:05:24,296
And Michael broke a two-month silence and went to visit his father.

117
00:05:24,308 --> 00:05:25,044
You came!

118
00:05:25,121 --> 00:05:26,308
Someone came!

119
00:05:26,490 --> 00:05:30,901
Only to tell you that the company is back on track and it's because you're behind bars.

120
00:05:30,969 --> 00:05:33,855
And now I get to do with my son what you never did with me.

121
00:05:33,943 --> 00:05:35,643
I'm taking him to the cabin.

122
00:05:35,734 --> 00:05:38,152
...scar, and every night they...

123
00:05:38,213 --> 00:05:41,120
I'm scarred, too, but my son is not going to be.

124
00:05:41,208 --> 00:05:45,288
...and they cover it with soap, and you're supposed to thank them,

125
00:05:45,371 --> 00:05:47,623
- like they're doing you a favor!
- That's all I came to say.

126
00:05:47,668 --> 00:05:50,045
Is there anything you'd like for me to pass on to the family?

127
00:05:50,188 --> 00:05:51,313
I'm your uncle!

128
00:05:51,939 --> 00:05:54,238
I'm your dad's twin brother.

129
00:05:55,078 --> 00:05:56,327
I'm Oscar!

130
00:05:56,532 --> 00:05:58,125
He switched on me.

131
00:05:58,395 --> 00:06:00,173
No one believes me.

132
00:06:00,250 --> 00:06:04,797
Unfortunately for Oscar, "You've got the wrong twin" was a very popular alibi.

133
00:06:04,888 --> 00:06:06,496
...you simply got the wrong twin!

134
00:06:06,578 --> 00:06:07,878
We're quadruplets.

135
00:06:07,950 --> 00:06:09,373
You got the wrong two.

136
00:06:09,461 --> 00:06:10,592
We're Larry and Dave.

137
00:06:10,663 --> 00:06:12,383
You want Curtis and Jack.

138
00:06:12,497 --> 00:06:15,691
I even started a Web site-- ImOscar.com.

139
00:06:16,469 --> 00:06:18,368
I'm innocent, Michael.

140
00:06:18,446 --> 00:06:19,613
I'm Oscar!

141
00:06:19,848 --> 00:06:21,087
.com!

142
00:06:22,916 --> 00:06:25,307
No, no, don't buy it. I'm taking my son to the cabin,

143
00:06:25,373 --> 00:06:29,028
and there's nothing you can say to make me believe that you are not my father.

144
00:06:30,144 --> 00:06:31,476
I understand.

145
00:06:32,684 --> 00:06:34,762
Your child comes first.

146
00:06:36,632 --> 00:06:38,337
Oh, my God, you're Oscar.

147
00:06:38,685 --> 00:06:39,904
.com!

148
00:06:45,126 --> 00:06:48,875
So Michael returned to the office to try and free his uncle,

149
00:06:51,767 --> 00:06:55,172
when he realized how much that freedom would cost his employees.

150
00:06:55,249 --> 00:06:58,910
Don't buy! We did it, Mikey! We're super rich again!

151
00:06:59,002 --> 00:07:01,285
And, I'm going to buy a car. The Volvo.

152
00:07:01,367 --> 00:07:04,624
Lindsay, you're not going to start spending money. And this is not a Volvo...

153
00:07:04,705 --> 00:07:06,057
Oh, that's from sitting on the copier.

154
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:08,269
- Lindsay, no...
- Michael, I've got nothing!

155
00:07:08,351 --> 00:07:10,767
My husband dumped me and ran off to Vegas with Kitty.

156
00:07:10,860 --> 00:07:12,478
That bleached blonde whore!

157
00:07:12,565 --> 00:07:13,809
Well, he's definitely got a type.

158
00:07:13,917 --> 00:07:15,248
I can't believe he left me.

159
00:07:15,341 --> 00:07:19,006
I mean, this, and these and this!

160
00:07:19,101 --> 00:07:20,338
That's the car.

161
00:07:20,420 --> 00:07:21,054
Oh.

162
00:07:21,187 --> 00:07:22,007
This.

163
00:07:22,370 --> 00:07:23,762
Glad I didn't spring for color.

164
00:07:23,849 --> 00:07:26,367
Lindsay, the only reason you want Tobias is because you can't have him.

165
00:07:26,375 --> 00:07:29,451
And the second that you can have something, all of a sudden you don't want it.

166
00:07:29,538 --> 00:07:31,033
That's not who I am, Michael.

167
00:07:31,139 --> 00:07:33,059
Well, all right, maybe you're right.

168
00:07:33,199 --> 00:07:34,740
Maybe we should get you this car.

169
00:07:34,904 --> 00:07:37,284
Yeah? I don't know, it's so boxy.

170
00:07:39,338 --> 00:07:40,096
Gob?

171
00:07:40,244 --> 00:07:41,452
Oh, Michael.

172
00:07:42,226 --> 00:07:43,081
How's Dad?

173
00:07:43,387 --> 00:07:46,285
Uh, I don't know. It's Oscar who is in prison,

174
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:49,767
and if I let him out, people will know that Dad is free and those people out there

175
00:07:49,849 --> 00:07:51,267
will end up paying for it.

176
00:07:51,431 --> 00:07:55,696
Dad hasn't tried to contact you, has he?

177
00:07:55,844 --> 00:07:58,599
Yeah, like I'd ever hear from that son of a bitch.

178
00:07:59,874 --> 00:08:02,982
Earlier that day, Gob received a letter from a group

179
00:08:03,058 --> 00:08:07,795
that reunited abandoned sons with their fathers-- called S.A.D.

180
00:08:07,882 --> 00:08:09,474
A father-son reunion?

181
00:08:10,633 --> 00:08:11,975
Dad's still in prison.

182
00:08:12,050 --> 00:08:14,077
But now the letter made sense.

183
00:08:14,258 --> 00:08:16,387
That son of a bitch.

184
00:08:16,514 --> 00:08:17,882
Law Offices of Barry Zuckerkorn.

185
00:08:17,994 --> 00:08:19,382
Hi, it's Michael Bluth for Barry.

186
00:08:19,510 --> 00:08:21,352
Barry went to Reno to see your father.

187
00:08:21,460 --> 00:08:24,107
Reno? He said he's been visiting my father in prison.

188
00:08:24,246 --> 00:08:26,785
Yeah, Barry says a lot of things he doesn't mean!

189
00:08:28,772 --> 00:08:31,271
Well, I guess I'm going to Reno to look for Dad.

190
00:08:31,353 --> 00:08:33,499
Good luck, favorite son.

191
00:08:34,363 --> 00:08:38,900
So once again Michael went after the father who'd once again abandoned him,

192
00:08:38,982 --> 00:08:42,827
only to find that he was about to do the same to his own son.

193
00:08:44,118 --> 00:08:45,853
It's not happening, is it?

194
00:08:46,012 --> 00:08:47,276
Something came up.

195
00:08:51,537 --> 00:08:54,905
Michael had just told his son they wouldn't be going to the cabin.

196
00:08:54,993 --> 00:08:56,226
Right, but the cabin's in Lake Tahoe.

197
00:08:56,288 --> 00:08:58,116
So I'm saying that's right near Reno. We could just...

198
00:08:58,172 --> 00:09:01,392
Yeah, but you know, this is going to be like an adult trip. Aunt Lindsay will be here. Hi.

199
00:09:01,499 --> 00:09:04,494
Hey, why don't you pop a tent in front with your cousin Maeby?

200
00:09:04,664 --> 00:09:05,478
What?! No!

201
00:09:05,565 --> 00:09:07,864
I'm not really the outdoorsy type.

202
00:09:07,951 --> 00:09:10,660
Well, then this is a good chance for you to rub off on her.

203
00:09:14,654 --> 00:09:16,962
As Michael set out to find his father,

204
00:09:17,060 --> 00:09:19,231
Gob thought he was doing the same.

205
00:09:19,966 --> 00:09:21,093
There's my guy!

206
00:09:23,107 --> 00:09:24,330
Hey, buddy, come on.

207
00:09:27,085 --> 00:09:29,014
Get them to track down your dad, too?

208
00:09:29,148 --> 00:09:31,226
My dad actually had them track me down.

209
00:09:32,938 --> 00:09:36,326
But it does look like he's not going to show.

210
00:09:37,632 --> 00:09:41,108
I kind of feel like that kid who found the severed hand.

211
00:09:42,119 --> 00:09:43,771
"Hey, Dad, look what I found!"

212
00:09:45,164 --> 00:09:47,258
Anything for his father's approval.

213
00:09:48,845 --> 00:09:50,157
Heartbreaking.

214
00:09:51,472 --> 00:09:52,777
You look familiar.

215
00:09:53,004 --> 00:09:55,251
I think that's because we actually kind of look alike.

216
00:09:55,370 --> 00:09:57,432
Remember when I said Gob had a son?

217
00:09:57,524 --> 00:09:58,334
I'm Gob.

218
00:09:58,468 --> 00:10:00,233
I wasn't just saying that.

219
00:10:00,335 --> 00:10:03,858
In high school, Gob became intimate with these girls.

220
00:10:03,961 --> 00:10:05,844
These girls got pregnant.

221
00:10:06,071 --> 00:10:07,828
This one had a baby.

222
00:10:07,945 --> 00:10:10,197
And that baby would grow up to be...

223
00:10:10,417 --> 00:10:11,604
- Steve Holt.
- Steve Holt!

224
00:10:12,306 --> 00:10:15,859
All I ever wanted was to spend a little time with my Dad.

225
00:10:15,912 --> 00:10:17,190
Maybe go camping.

226
00:10:17,233 --> 00:10:19,009
But I guess that'll never happen.

227
00:10:19,182 --> 00:10:21,864
Look, I know this is going to sound kind of crazy, but

228
00:10:21,963 --> 00:10:24,767
my family actually has a cabin in the woods for one more night.

229
00:10:24,871 --> 00:10:27,379
Maybe we could go up to Reno, get the keys and go camping.

230
00:10:27,461 --> 00:10:31,465
You know, sort of a son-and-son thing.

231
00:10:31,614 --> 00:10:34,629
If Steve had had a father, he would've warned him not to go

232
00:10:34,690 --> 00:10:37,809
into the woods with strange men, but he didn't.

233
00:10:37,937 --> 00:10:38,771
Sure!

234
00:10:38,900 --> 00:10:39,990
- Let's go!
- Okay!

235
00:10:40,774 --> 00:10:42,602
- This is me right here.
- Oh, okay.

236
00:10:42,688 --> 00:10:44,071
- Camping!
- Whoo!

237
00:10:44,747 --> 00:10:47,154
Michael, meanwhile, arrived in Reno,

238
00:10:47,261 --> 00:10:52,999
a city competing with Las Vegas' successful "What Happens in Vegas Stays in Vegas" campaign,

239
00:10:53,105 --> 00:10:56,104
and set about searching for Barry Zuckerkorn.

240
00:10:56,216 --> 00:11:00,753
I'm looking for a man who's probably in the seedy underbelly of Reno.

241
00:11:00,864 --> 00:11:04,443
Oh, the Christian League had The Seedy Underbelly shut down.

242
00:11:04,597 --> 00:11:06,149
Now it's a Swallows.

243
00:11:06,231 --> 00:11:09,394
Swallows was a family-style restaurant by day

244
00:11:09,487 --> 00:11:12,890
- and an anything-goes, pan-sexual bazaar by night.
- Hello, and welcome to Swallows.

245
00:11:12,897 --> 00:11:16,169
Can I interest you in a smoothie or an amyl... Michael!

246
00:11:16,388 --> 00:11:20,582
Tobias, I thought that you were in Vegas with Kitty in the Blue Man Group.

247
00:11:20,664 --> 00:11:26,306
No, as it turns out, the part that I'd destroyed my life to get had already been cast.

248
00:11:26,369 --> 00:11:30,842
The role was filled by George Sr., who used it to hide in plain sight.

249
00:11:30,934 --> 00:11:33,151
That is, until he choked on a marshmallow

250
00:11:33,157 --> 00:11:36,771
and almost died, when no one noticed he'd turned blue.

251
00:11:36,905 --> 00:11:41,032
So Kitty suggested we come up here to try out in Reno, and...

252
00:11:41,119 --> 00:11:42,711
Oh, I'll be honest, Michael.

253
00:11:42,920 --> 00:11:47,309
Leaving Lindsay was the biggest little mistake I've ever made.

254
00:11:47,421 --> 00:11:50,852
I can't seem to call her, though. Damn, this pride of mine!

255
00:11:50,990 --> 00:11:53,950
Tuna melt's up, and you need to flip the cushions in the grind room.

256
00:11:54,026 --> 00:11:55,112
Yes, sir. Right away, sir.

257
00:11:55,183 --> 00:11:58,461
Oh, great, now I'm going to be smelling to high heaven like a tuna melt.

258
00:11:58,531 --> 00:12:02,536
Tobias, what would you say if I told you that Lindsay might be willing to get back together with you?

259
00:12:02,627 --> 00:12:04,794
Oh, uh, I'll call her right now!

260
00:12:04,809 --> 00:12:07,047
Actually, why don't you let me handle it? You know Lindsay.

261
00:12:07,053 --> 00:12:09,254
- She only wants what she can't have.
- Right.

262
00:12:09,349 --> 00:12:11,906
- What would you do about Kitty?
- I can't lie to you, Michael.

263
00:12:12,998 --> 00:12:15,176
Kitty left me two days ago.

264
00:12:15,299 --> 00:12:17,517
There's a blue hand print on the back of your head, Kitty.

265
00:12:17,589 --> 00:12:18,945
Are you seeing someone else?

266
00:12:19,011 --> 00:12:21,890
