308
00:14:01,428 --> 00:14:04,480
I know that Oscar is in prison, and that my father is a Blue Man,

309
00:14:04,551 --> 00:14:06,272
and that you are clearly in cahoots with him.

310
00:14:06,343 --> 00:14:07,741
Ooh, a lot.

311
00:14:07,842 --> 00:14:08,541
Yeah, where is he?

312
00:14:08,606 --> 00:14:12,170
I don't know. I was gonna meet him here, but he must have seen you and run off.

313
00:14:12,267 --> 00:14:16,451
I was gonna give him this: $250,000 and a passport.

314
00:14:17,128 --> 00:14:18,007
Just a passport.

315
00:14:18,104 --> 00:14:19,804
I was up for so long.

316
00:14:20,041 --> 00:14:21,555
Barry, you're fired.

317
00:14:22,429 --> 00:14:23,410
What?

318
00:14:24,438 --> 00:14:25,667
Just like that?

319
00:14:25,866 --> 00:14:26,881
No warning?

320
00:14:26,988 --> 00:14:28,257
You're my only client.

321
00:14:28,370 --> 00:14:29,517
What am I supposed to do now?

322
00:14:29,619 --> 00:14:30,925
Turn tricks on the street?

323
00:14:31,022 --> 00:14:32,523
How much you think I can get for that, by the way?

324
00:14:32,605 --> 00:14:34,612
All right, this is crazy. I've got to let Oscar out of prison.

325
00:14:34,699 --> 00:14:35,871
What about making out?

326
00:14:36,173 --> 00:14:38,672
$50, or is that just L.A.? Am I just...?

327
00:14:44,594 --> 00:14:49,397
Soon, Lindsay arrived at the hotel, and the kids finally faced facts.

328
00:14:49,874 --> 00:14:51,861
Look, it was just a half-kiss, all right?

329
00:14:51,927 --> 00:14:53,740
Maybe that's the reason why we're acting weird.

330
00:14:53,827 --> 00:14:55,410
It's because we didn't finish the kiss?

331
00:14:55,505 --> 00:14:56,509
Is that where...

332
00:14:56,638 --> 00:14:57,897
- Yeah.
- Yeah, I mean...

333
00:14:57,990 --> 00:14:59,711
Do you think we should just finish the kiss, get it out of the way?

334
00:14:59,793 --> 00:15:01,342
Let's get it out of the way!

335
00:15:03,499 --> 00:15:06,150
Hey, kids! Bring the bags, we're sharing a room!

336
00:15:06,264 --> 00:15:08,111
All right, let's meet back here tomorrow morning.

337
00:15:08,224 --> 00:15:09,048
- Okay?
- Yeah.

338
00:15:09,314 --> 00:15:10,289
- Go.
- Oh, you...

339
00:15:10,841 --> 00:15:14,711
Yeah, I'm gonna, um, I'm gonna stay out here and, uh,

340
00:15:14,809 --> 00:15:17,148
and watch that famous Reno sunset.

341
00:15:18,695 --> 00:15:20,231
Isn't it behind you?

342
00:15:21,634 --> 00:15:23,820
There's... Yeah, but there's mirrors.

343
00:15:23,990 --> 00:15:25,514
It'll actually look closer...

344
00:15:25,537 --> 00:15:29,641
While George Michael waited for the sunset, another set of sons arrived.

345
00:15:29,653 --> 00:15:31,172
Michael said he'd meet me here.

346
00:15:31,239 --> 00:15:34,311
I guess I'll get the keys to the cabin... son.

347
00:15:34,957 --> 00:15:37,797
I'll go buy some fishing stuff... son.

348
00:15:38,587 --> 00:15:40,260
So where did you get this kid?

349
00:15:40,347 --> 00:15:41,699
Yeah, I guess I can tell you now.

350
00:15:41,992 --> 00:15:45,390
We were both waiting for our dads at that garden where the little boy found the arm.

351
00:15:45,785 --> 00:15:47,812
The kid's amazing, though. It's almost like...

352
00:15:48,269 --> 00:15:50,081
I wish he could be my dad.

353
00:15:50,172 --> 00:15:53,670
Okay, um, your dad's not trying to find you-- your son is.

354
00:15:53,726 --> 00:15:54,651
That kid's your son.

355
00:15:54,718 --> 00:15:55,726
You're the dad.

356
00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:57,218
Hmm?

357
00:16:02,948 --> 00:16:05,050
I've made a huge, tiny mistake.

358
00:16:05,138 --> 00:16:08,948
No, no, G-G-Gob, Gob, you can't just leave your son in the middle of a parking lot in Reno.

359
00:16:09,045 --> 00:16:12,558
And that's when Michael saw his own son in a parking lot in Reno.

360
00:16:12,645 --> 00:16:15,394
He drove all the way up here to be with me. Wow.

361
00:16:16,075 --> 00:16:19,393
Well, I guess I'm, uh, I'm no better than...

362
00:16:22,573 --> 00:16:23,673
No, I'm better.

363
00:16:24,042 --> 00:16:27,554
They were an hour out of Reno when George Michael woke up.

364
00:16:27,638 --> 00:16:30,799
You were out like a light. Pal, our dreams are about to come true.

365
00:16:30,872 --> 00:16:31,583
Maeby?

366
00:16:31,666 --> 00:16:33,791
Definitely! We are going camping.

367
00:16:33,990 --> 00:16:35,229
It's finally happening.

368
00:16:36,840 --> 00:16:38,408
It's never happening.

369
00:16:40,646 --> 00:16:44,159
Michael had just surprised his sleeping son by taking him camping.

370
00:16:44,225 --> 00:16:46,621
I put this off too long, and it's too important.

371
00:16:46,688 --> 00:16:49,340
Your Uncle Oscar can stay in prison one more day, right?

372
00:16:49,453 --> 00:16:52,765
Not according to that day's blog on Imoscar.com.

373
00:16:52,863 --> 00:16:55,746
This here is way more important than me trying to find my father.

374
00:16:55,817 --> 00:16:58,837
Although, I was very close. I almost had Pop Up in Reno.

375
00:16:59,899 --> 00:17:00,804
Me, too.

376
00:17:01,440 --> 00:17:05,028
As Michael was forcibly taking his son out to the cabin,

377
00:17:05,110 --> 00:17:08,336
Lucille was ready to forcibly throw hers out.

378
00:17:20,562 --> 00:17:22,365
Well, that was a freebie.

379
00:17:22,477 --> 00:17:26,096
Lucille didn't trust herself to be in the house when Buster returned,

380
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:29,830
so she headed off to the cabin Michael said would be unoccupied.

381
00:17:29,912 --> 00:17:33,066
Tobias, meanwhile, was looking for a way to make his wife jealous

382
00:17:33,147 --> 00:17:37,509
by convincing her that he was not only a Blue Man, but still with Kitty,

383
00:17:37,607 --> 00:17:41,995
when he came across a makeup woman, who, coincidentally, looked a great deal like Kitty.

384
00:17:42,082 --> 00:17:47,633
If this tableau I recreate, perhaps I can re-snare my mate.

385
00:17:47,945 --> 00:17:50,227
Gee, why wouldn't she want him back?

386
00:17:50,372 --> 00:17:53,909
And Michael and his son arrived at the cabin in the woods.

387
00:17:55,625 --> 00:17:58,503
Looks like they have trucked off the bedrooms.

388
00:17:58,584 --> 00:18:02,455
Maybe we'll just set up some sleeping bags right here in the living room, huh?

389
00:18:02,553 --> 00:18:06,014
Lucille, meanwhile, heard a familiar sound.

390
00:18:06,895 --> 00:18:09,414
Oh, come on!

391
00:18:09,490 --> 00:18:10,243
Mother?

392
00:18:10,371 --> 00:18:12,971
What the hell are you doing back there?

393
00:18:13,044 --> 00:18:16,459
I decided to sleep in the car, so my snoring wouldn't bother you,

394
00:18:16,664 --> 00:18:20,329
and I left that recording of my snoring so you wouldn't know I'm gone.

395
00:18:20,754 --> 00:18:22,162
We're halfway to the cabin.

396
00:18:22,264 --> 00:18:24,563
I'm going to drop you by this light.

397
00:18:24,912 --> 00:18:26,382
Or I could come with you.

398
00:18:26,643 --> 00:18:30,028
That might be the exact shot in the arm our relationship needs.

399
00:18:30,125 --> 00:18:33,944
Well, at least I'll have someone to talk to on the way up.

400
00:18:43,093 --> 00:18:44,348
This is fun, isn't it?

401
00:18:44,465 --> 00:18:47,184
This is just like when we used to live up in the attic.

402
00:18:47,266 --> 00:18:48,070
Yeah.

403
00:18:50,056 --> 00:18:52,815
Or, or we could go back to Reno.

404
00:18:52,929 --> 00:18:54,199
Go back to Reno?

405
00:18:54,890 --> 00:18:56,319
You don't want to be here?

406
00:18:56,411 --> 00:19:00,399
I mean, you've been sleeping in the stair car just so we could spend time together.

407
00:19:00,584 --> 00:19:02,207
That's not totally true, though.

408
00:19:02,371 --> 00:19:04,361
I'm just in the middle of a problem right now.

409
00:19:04,460 --> 00:19:06,272
Oh, yeah? Well, let's... let's talk about it.

410
00:19:06,364 --> 00:19:07,798
I can't talk about it with you.

411
00:19:08,039 --> 00:19:08,950
Why not?

412
00:19:09,082 --> 00:19:11,367
It's just, it's about a girl, and you're not gonna like this.

413
00:19:11,454 --> 00:19:13,246
